{
  "texts": [
    "These concerns can be mitigated to some extent by technologies such as Augmented Reality (AR) and Remote Maintenance (RM) (Masoni et al., 2017; Mourtzis et al., 2017), and can enable faster training of the workforce and provide real-time assistance on the shopfloor.",
    "To analyze data from the shopfloor, data-driven PHM methods have successfully used sensor measurements to detect faults and predict the Remaining Useful Life (RUL) of systems.",
    "Sensor signals are often numerical or image-based, and AI models have been fine-tuned for such modes of data.",
    "While this addresses some of the requirements of the fourth challenge of modern maintenance, it does not tackle all modes of data.",
    "One part of maintenance that contains troves of data but is yet to be exploited, is the technical text data stored in Maintenance Work Orders (MWOs)."
  ]
}